adv java-50 days

jdbc-overcome drawback from jdbc-platform independent
odbc drawback only supported in windows - platform dependent


diff b/n odbc and jdbc
1.defn
2.microsoft,sun micro systems
3. used for langs like c,c++,java,etc           used for java only
4.most odbc drivers are developed in c and c++           in java
5.odbc can be used for java but low performance


drivers
Type 1: JDBC ODBC bridge driver or bridge driver
-java appl <--> JDBC ODBC bridge driver <--> odbc <--> database
-only supports until 1.7 version
-not recommended
Type 2:
Type 3:
Type 4: we currently use this - purely dev by java

thin driver - no extra comp req to communicate with DB eg.Type 4 driver
thick driver - extra comp like ODBC driver or vendor specific native libraries or middleware server is req.  eg. Type 1,2,3 drivers

steps to prepare jdbc appln
-----------------------------
------------------------------

-4 jdbc comps. : translator/driver, connection, stmt obj, result set

1. load and register the driver
2. connection establishment b/n java specific calls to db specific calls
3. create stmt object 
4. prepare, send and execute sql query to the data
5. process result from result set
6. close the connection


1. load and register the driver
--------------------------------
-optional
-the forName() method of a class is used to register the driver class. This method is used to dynamically load the driver class.

syntax for forName() method
----------------------------
public static void forName()(String ClassName) throws ClassNotFoundException.
class.forName("com.msql.cj.jdbc.Driver");

2. connection establishment b/n java specific calls to db specific calls
==========================================================================
the getConnection() method of a DriverManager class is used to establish connection with db.

syntax
--------
public static connection getConnection(String url, String username, String password);
url="jdbc:mysql>//localhost:3306/database-name";
username="root";
password="root";

eg: Connection con=DriverManager.getConnection(url,usernme,password);


3. create stmt object 
========================

public Statement createStatement();
eg: Statement st=con.createStstement();

4. prepare, send and execute sql query to the data
===================================================

String sqlQuery=st.executeUpdate("use non-select opetaions"); --> return type is always int
String sqlQuery=st.executeQuery("for select opetaions"); --> return type is ResultSet;
String sqlQuery=st.execute("both select and non-select opetaions"); --> return type is Boolean
if true --> for selectQuery
if false --> non-selectQuery



5. process result from result set
=======================================
-only used for select operations (retrievable operations) 
-2 ways: index and column wise
eg: eno,ename,esal,eaddr
while(rs.next()({
System.out.println(rs.getInt(1)+"----"+rs.getString(2)+"----"+rs.getDouble(3)+"----"+rs.getString(4));

System.out.println(rs.getInt(eno)+"----"+rs.getString(ename)+"----"+rs.getDouble(esal)+"----"+rs.getString(eaddr));
}


6. close the connection
========================
con.close();

